 giving forms such as <i>Ma(h)auld</i>. <i>Maud</i> or <i>Matilda</i> was also the name of the daughter (  1102–67 ) of  Henry I  of England; she was married early in life to the Holy Roman Emperor  Henry V , and later disputed the throne of England with her cousin  Stephen . In  1128  she married  Geoffrey , Count of Anjou. A medieval chronicler commented, ‘she was a good woman, but she had little bliss with him’. The name <i>Maud</i> became quite common in England in the 19th century, when its popularity was influenced in part by  Tennyson's  poem Maud, published in  1855 , but has not been much used since the early decades of the 20th century."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Maud Pirot was born in 1144, in England. She had at least 1 son with Ralph Perot. She died after 1165."},"et":{"1144–Aft 1165":"1144–pärast 1165","1140–1195":"1140–1195","1165–1222":"1165–1222","1144–1165":"1144–1165","Aft 1165":"pärast 1165","1222":"1222","1144":"1144","1165":"1165","1195":"1195","1140":"1140","Hawkwell, Essex, England":"Hawkwell, Essex, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"1144–Aft 1165":"1144–1165 jälkeen","1140–1195":"1140–1195","1165–1222":"1165–1222","1144–1165":"1144–1165","Aft 1165":"1165 jälkeen","1222":"1222","1144":"1144","1165":"1165","1195":"1195","1140":"1140","Hawkwell, Essex, England":"Hawkwell, Essex, England","England":"England"},"fr":{"1144–Aft 1165":"1144–après 1165","1140–1195":"1140–1195","1165–1222":"1165–1222","1144–1165":"1144–1165","Aft 1165":"après 1165","1222":"1222","1144":"1144","1165":"1165","1195":"1195","1140":"1140","Hawkwell, Essex, England":"Hawkwell, Essex, Angleterre","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Maud Pirot est née en 1144, à Angleterre. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Ralph Perot. Elle est décédée après 1165."},"de":{"1144–Aft 1165":"1144–nach 1165","1140–1195":"1140–1195","1165–1222":"1165–1222","1144–1165":"1144–1165","Aft 1165":"nach 1165","1222":"1222","1144":"1144","1165":"1165","1195":"1195","1140":"1140","Hawkwell, Essex,